Hartbeespoort Community Policing Forum spokesperson said: The biker from Krugersdorp drove out to Hartbeespoort on Sunday and did not return home. Passers-by noticed a motorcycle wreck along the Hartebeeshoek road on Monday morning and upon closer inspection, found the body, still wearing his helmet, wedged in a tree. It seems the bike hit a tree, and the biker was flung into it.An inquest docket has been opened by the Hartbeespoort police. Caxton News Service Read original story on kormorant.co.za